{
  "texts": [
    "The general form of the bulk-bulk propagator isG h n,S (η 1, η 2, k) = Φ h n,S (η 1, k)Φ h * n,S (η 2, k)θ(η 1 -η 2) + (η 1 ↔ η 2) - Φ h n,S (η 0, k) Φ * n,S (η 0, k) Φ h * n,S (η 1, k)Φ h * n,S (η 2, k), (3.41)where the mode functions Φ h n,S are related to Φ h |h|,S by (2.36).",
    "Indeed, we can use this relationship iteratively to writeΦ h n,S (η, k) = Dh,n (iη, k)Φ h |h|,S (η, k), n > |h|, (3.42) JHEP05(2024)196where Dh,n (x, k) are real differential operators in x with k-dependent coefficients.",
    "It follows that Dh,n (iη, k) are purely real after Wick rotation.",
    "Furthermore, they are either purely even in x and therefore purely real when written in terms of η (if n -|h| is even) or purely odd in x and therefore purely imaginary when written in terms of η (if n -|h| is odd).",
    "This final property follows from the fact that the B m,n in (2.36) are real and only non-zero when n and m differ by an even number."
  ]
}